away from Southern Slavery\n|first=Henry\n|last=Goings\n|publisher=[[University of Virginia Press]]\n|year=2012\n|isbn=978-0813932408\n|url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Rambles_of_a_Runaway_from_Southern_Slave.html?id=bpuMd7z3klIC\n|editor1-first=Calvin\n|editor1-last=Schermerhorn\n|editor2-first=Michael\n|editor2-last=Plunkett\n|editor3-first=Edward\n|editor3-last=Gaynor}}\n* {{cite book\n|title=Before Freedom When I Just Can Remember: Twenty-seven Oral Histories of Former South Carolina Slaves\n|editor-first=Belinda\n|editor-last=Hurmence\n|date=1989\n|isbn=978-0-89587-069-8\n|publisher=[[Blair]]}}\n[[File:IncidentsInTheLifeOfASlaveGirl.jpg|thumb]]\n* {{cite book\n|title=Before Freedom: Forty-Eight Oral Histories of Former North & South Carolina Slaves\n|editor-first=Belinda\n|editor-last=Hurmence\n|publisher=[[Mentor Books]]\n|year=1990\n|isbn=978-0-451-62781-0}}\n* {{cite book\n|title=My Folks Don't Want Me to Talk about Slavery: Twenty-One Oral Histories of Former North Carolina Slaves\n|editor-first=Belinda\n|editor-last=Hurmence\n|year=1990 \n}}\n* {{cite book\n|title=Slavery Time When I Was Chillun\n|url=https://archive.org/details/slaverytimewheni00beli\n|url-access=registration\n|year=1997\n|publisher=[[G. P. Putnam's Sons]]\n|isbn=978-0399231940\n|editor-first=Belinda\n|editor-last=Hurmence}}\n* {{cite book\n|title=We Lived in a Little Cabin in the Yard: Personal Accounts of Slavery in Virginia\n|date=1994\n|editor-first=Belinda\n|editor-last=Hurmence\n|publisher=[[Blair]]\n\n|isbn=978-0895871183}}\n* {{cite book\n|title=Incidents in the Life of a Slave Girl, Written by Herself\n|first=Harriet Ann\n|last=Jacobs\n|publisher=[[Thayer & Eldridge]]\n|date=1861\n|url=https://amerautobiofa14.wiki.uml.edu/file/view/Excerpts+from+Incidents+in+the+Life+of+a+Slave+Girl+--+Jacobs.pdf\n|editor-first=L. Maria\n|editor-last=Child}}\n* {{cite book\n|title=God Struck Me Dead, Voices of Ex-Slaves\n|first=Clifton H.\n|last=Johnson\n|year=1993\n|publisher=[[Pilgrim 